cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a deep learning model for sleep staging, which involves the analysis of polysomnogram (PSG) data. The model combines deep learning with expert-defined rules to generate simple, interpretable models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). However, given the focus on deep learning and the use of convolutional neural networks, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The use of PSG data also suggests a potential fit with cs.NE, while the focus on interpretability could align with cs.HC. Finally, the use of convolutional neural networks suggests a potential fit with cs.CV.
